      "message": "Good question. I looked into this. Based on the following Web pages, what we call \"bps\" (bits per sample) here is called \"bpp\" (bits per pixel) by others:\n\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Color_depth\nhttps://wiki.videolan.org/YUV\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chroma_subsampling#4:2:0 (search for \"bits/component\" and \"bits/pixel\")\n\nThe AV1 spec also uses the term \"sample\" as a sample of a component (Y, U, or V) of a pixel. So I think our use of the term \"bps\" in the aom_image_t struct is nonstandard. I don\u0027t know if we can rename the \"bps\" field to \"bpp\" or \"bits_per_pixel\" without breaking backward compatibility.\n\nI have renamed the new variable I introduced to \"bit_depth\". It is also not ideal, because it differs from the meaning of \"bit depth\" in the AV1 spec. So I added a comment to point that out.",
